  "bio_raw": "Shah Jafor Sadeek Quaderi is currently serving as a lecturer in University of Liberal Arts Bangladesh. He has teaching experience as lecturer at City University and Asian University of Bangladesh. During his postgraduation, he conducted research in Information Retrieval based on Review Helpfulness Prediction using Natural Language Processing and Machine Learning Models, and his undergraduate research was in Intelligent Traffic Management Systems. He worked as a Graduate Research Assistant in AISIP Lab, ICT Division Funded Project, Bangladesh. Besides, he served as a Graduate Research Assistant in the Artificial Intelligence Lab at, the University of Malaya, Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia, and worked as an Undergraduate Teaching Assistant during his undergraduate. He likes to enrich his portfolio with dynamic research activities with publications.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Information  Retrieval, Natural  Language, Machine  Learning, Data  Mining, Intelligent  Traffic  Management  Systems."
  ],
  "education": [
    {
      "raw": "Education\nMSc  in  Computer  Science\n,  University  of  Malaya,  Kuala  Lumpur,  Malaysia.\nBSc  in  Computer  Science  and  Engineering\n,  East  West  University,  Dhaka,  Bangladesh."
    }
  ],
  "publications_raw": [
    "Journal Articles\nAhmed, M., &\nQuaderi, S. J. S.\n(2024). Psychological Status Observation Among the Medical Students using DASS21. Bangladesh Journal of Medical Science, 23(4), 1149-1158.\nQuaderi, S. J. S.\n, & Varathan, K. D. (2024). “Identification of significant features and machine learning technique in predicting helpful reviews.”. PeerJ Computer Science, 10, e1745.\nQuaderi, S. J. S.\n, Labonno, S. A., Mostafa, S., & Akhter, S. (2022). \"Identify The Beehive Sound Using Deep Learning.\" International Journal of Computer Science & Information Technology, Volume 14, Number 4.\nShamim Akhter, M., Ahsan, N.,\nQuaderi, S. J. S.\n, Al Forhad, M. A., Sumit, S. H., & Rahman, M. R. (2020). “A SUMO based simulation framework for intelligent traffic management system.” Journal of Traffic and Logistics Engineering Vol, 8(1).\nAkhter, S., Ahsan, M. N., &\nQuaderi, S. J. S.\n(2019). Modeling ant colony optimization for multi-agent based intelligent transportation system. International Journal of Advanced Computer Science and Applications, 10(10).",
